cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.HC

This paper deals with analyzing Yelp ratings and correcting for biases in the data. The most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper focuses on analyzing social network data. The second likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper deals with analyzing and correcting for biases in ratings data. The third likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the paper discusses the impact of Yelp ratings on local businesses. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) as the paper deals with analyzing social network data and its impact on behavior. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the paper discusses the impact of Yelp ratings on user behavior and decision-making.
